THOUGHT: The incorrect fold happens in InstCombineSelect.cpp where select-of-fcmp is converted to fmaxnum/fminnum. We need to add a guard to skip this transform if fast-math flags include ninf (hasNoInfs), because rewriting to min/max unconditionally evaluates the input and can produce poison for -inf that was previously guarded. I will inspect the relevant section and insert a check for FMF.hasNoInfs() before performing the transformation, then submit the patch.

```bash
nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp | sed -n '3650,3705p' && sed -i '3663,3700{s/// a fmaxnum/fminnum intrinsic\./// a fmaxnum/fminnum intrinsic.
  // Avoid folding to fmin/fmax when fast-math disallows infinities (ninf),
  // as it may turn a guarded poison (e.g., -inf in the non-selected arm)
  // into unconditional poison by evaluating min/max unconditionally.
  FastMathFlags FMF = I.getFastMathFlags();
  if (FMF.hasNoInfs())
    return nullptr;/}' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp && submit-patch
```

